    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:1.1",
          "pli": "“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī”ti. ",
          "en": "“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And I live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:1.2",
          "pli": "Cuddasamaṃ. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:1.3",
          "pli": "Dutiyo vaggo. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:2.1",
          "pli": "Mahābhiññaṃ iddhi dibbaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:2.2",
          "pli": "Cetopariyaṃ ṭhānaṃ kammaṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:2.3",
          "pli": "Sabbatthadhātudhimutti, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:2.4",
          "pli": "Indriyaṃ jhānaṃ tisso vijjāti. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.24:2.5",
          "pli": "Anuruddhasaṃyuttaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": "The Linked Discourses with Anuruddha are the eighth section."
        }
      ],
